Leighton Unit Awarded $518 Million Iraq Crude Oil Project

-- B y   V i c t o r i a   B a t c h e l o r
-- 
2011-10-13T22:09:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/leighton-unit-awarded-518-million-iraq-crude-oil-project.html
Leighton Holdings Ltd. (LEI) ’s unit
Leighton Offshore has been awarded a contract by  Iraq ’s South
Oil Company. The $518 million contract forms part of the Crude
Oil Export Facility Reconstruction Project, which is financed
and supported through the Japanese official development
assistance loan by Japan International Cooperation Agency. The
project involves the development of two offshore platforms, an
oil pipeline and a Single Point Mooring system, the company said
in a regulatory filing.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Victoria Batchelor at 
 vbatchelor@bloomberg.net  